    <title type="text">Nestle-Aland 28 Online</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.nestle-aland.com/">Nestle-Aland Novum Testamentum
      Graece</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><img
      alt="http://www.nestle-aland.com/fileadmin/templates/nestlealand/gfx/logo-nestlealand.png"
      class="decoded"
      src="http://www.nestle-aland.com/fileadmin/templates/nestlealand/gfx/logo-nestlealand.png"
      /></span><br /><h1><span style="font-size: x-small;">The 28th
      edition</span></h1></blockquote><div
      class="csc-textpic-text"><blockquote><span style="font-size: x-small;">The 28th
      edition of the Nestle-Aland had to accomplish two different tasks. First, the apparatus had to
      be revised thoroughly to give it more clarity and make it easier to use. Secondly, the
      text-critical in-sights and decisions resulting from work on the Editio Critica Maior of the
      Greek New Testament had to be incorporated. As a consequence of these alterations, which so far
      concern only the Catholic Letters, the Nestle-Aland has for the first time in its history a
      different presentation for different parts of the text. The Catholic Letters were revised
      according to a fundamentally new concept which in the long run will be adopted for the entire
      edition. The revision of the remaining texts was confined to a thorough inspection and
      rearrangement of the apparatus, while the basic structure was left untouched. Another important
      innovation is that from now on the Nestle-Aland will not appear only as a printed book, but
      also in digital form. </span><br /> <span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Changes in
      NA28</span></span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;">1. Revision
      and Correction of the Whole Edition </span><br /><ul><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Newly discovered Papyri
      listed</span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">Distinction
      between consistently cited witnesses of the first and second order
      abandoned</span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">Apparatus
      notes systematically checked</span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">Imprecise notes abandoned</span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Previously concatenated notes now cited
      separately</span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">Inserted
      Latin texts reduced and translated</span></li><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">References thoroughly revised</span></li></ul><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://www.nestle-aland.com/en/the-28-edition/revision-and-correction-of-the-whole-edition/">View
      details</a></span><br /> <span style="font-size: x-small;"> 2. Revision
      of the Catholic Letters </span><br /><ul><li><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">New reconstruction of the text</span></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Defining the Consistently Cited Witnesses for the Catholic
      Letters</span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a
      href="http://www.nestle-aland.com/en/the-28-edition/revision-of-the-catholic-letters/">View
      details</a></span><br /> </blockquote><nav
